0 SING~
Syntax: sing <song name>

Before you can use a song, you have to practice it.  The more you practice,
the higher chance you have of success when using.  Using songs costs mana.

Songs don't have any target, they affect everyone in the room. So, be careful
when singing a song in a room full of monsters.

If the song name is more than one word, then you must quote the song name.
Example: sing 'song of huma'.  Quoting is optional for single-word song.
You can abbreviate the song name.

Some examples:
  sing 'song of huma'             will start singing 'song of huma'
  sing knights                    will start singing 'knights ride forth'

See also the help sections for individual songs.
~

0 USE~
Syntax: use <skill> <target>

Before you can use a skill, you have to practice it.  The more you practice,
the higher chance you have of success when using.  Using skills costs nothing
except for some, which costs mana/psp or moves.

The <target> is optional.  Many skills which need targets will use an
appropriate default target, especially during combat.

If the skill name is more than one word, then you must quote the skill name.
Example: use 'shield clea' frag.  Quoting is optional for single-word skill.
You can abbreviate the skill name.

Some examples:
  use meditate                    will use meditate on user
  use 'shield cleave' victim      will use 'shield cleave' on victim

See also the help sections for individual skills.
~

0 PSI~
Syntax: psi <power> <target>

Before you can use a power, you have to practice it.  The more you practice,
the higher chance you have of success when using.  Using powers costs psp.
The psp cost decreases as your level increases.

The <target> is optional.  Many powers which need targets will use an
appropriate default target, especially during combat.

If the power name is more than one word, then you must quote the power name.
Example: psi 'ballistic attack' frag. Quoting is optional for single-word power.
You can abbreviate the power name.

When you use an offensive power, the victim usually gets a saving throw.
The effect of the power is reduced or eliminated if the victim makes the
saving throw successfully.

Some examples:
  psi endure                    will use endure on caster
  psi 'mind thrust' victim      will use 'mind thrust' on victim

See also the help sections for individual power.
~

0 CAST~
Syntax: cast <spell> <target> <casting level>

Before you can cast a spell, you have to practice it.  The more you practice,
the higher chance you have of success when casting.  Casting spells costs mana.
The mana cost decreases as your level increases.

The <target> is optional.  Many spells which need targets will use an
appropriate default target, especially during combat.

The <casting level> is optional. Many spells have casting level higher than 1,
and you don't have to cast spells at maximum casting level.

If the spell name is more than one word, then you must quote the spell name.
Example: cast 'cure critic' frag.  Quoting is optional for single-word spells.
You can abbreviate the spell name.

When you cast an offensive spell, the victim usually gets a saving throw.
The effect of the spell is reduced or eliminated if the victim makes the
saving throw successfully.

Some examples:
  cast 'chill touch' victim 4  will cast 'chill touch' level 4 on victim
  cast armor newbie 3  will cast armor level 3 on newbie
  cast fireball 4  will cast fireball level 4 on current target if already 
    in combat
  cast 'floating disc' 2  will cast 'floating disc' level 2 on caster

See also the help sections for individual spells.
Use the 'spells' command to see the spells you already have (help spells).
~

